<br>
Its funny how some things are &quot;addictions&quot; and others are not.  We are dependant on eating, sleeping, driving, and yet these are not addictions (I realize that these are examples or stuff we need to do to survive but they fit the dictionaries meaning of the word).  It is also funny how some things are considered hobbies instead of addictions.  I consider EQ and playing video games in general as a hobby.  Its something I like to do a lot, and its fun.  I also like to read books.  I pick up a book and I can't put it down....but I'm not addicted reading am I?<br>
<br>
People throw around the word &quot;addiction&quot; when they see something they don't like or are looking for a reason to place blame somewhere else.  Like the woman about her sons death.<br>
